>>modify dat 'eqs' [vdat wdat]
>>Fills the value of dat array according to the formula in string 'eqs'.
>>Formula is an arbitrary expression depending on variables x, y, z, u,
>>v, w. Coordinates x, y, z are supposed to be normalized in interval
>>[0,1]. Variable u is the original value of the array (see also Sec.
>>18). If optional data vdat, wdat (must be the same size as dat) is
>>specified then variables v and w denote its values else it are zero.




